1
00:00:01,640 --> 00:00:03,530
Your lives...? Hey...

2
00:00:04,300 --> 00:00:06,050
This is getting vicious.

3
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:08,440
Even though that's not 
something you bet on...

4
00:00:09,190 --> 00:00:10,510
That's our Yukino-kun!

5
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:13,210
That's why she's part of Sabertooth!

6
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:15,230
Good luck, Yukino!

7
00:00:15,710 --> 00:00:17,260
This is getting interesting.

8
00:00:17,770 --> 00:00:20,330
Does that Yukino chick have all her marbles?

9
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:22,310
Kagura-san...

10
00:00:22,710 --> 00:00:25,970
Even though her opponent is Kagura, 
the strongest wizard of Mermaid Heel,

11
00:00:26,210 --> 00:00:28,270
it seems she's got confidence to spare.

12
00:02:04,050 --> 00:02:06,140
If you are sincerely prepared to do this,

13
00:02:07,190 --> 00:02:09,310
then accepting it is the proper thing to do.

14
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:14,970
Fine. Come and get me.

15
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,310
Kagura versus Yukino!

16
00:02:22,990 --> 00:02:23,800
Seriously?!

17
00:02:24,170 --> 00:02:27,350
They bet their lives, so 
whoever loses dies, right?!

18
00:02:27,430 --> 00:02:28,500
Can they do that?!

19
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:32,130
Well, things have taken a serious turn.

20
00:02:32,710 --> 00:02:34,320
Just what's going on here?!

21
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:39,040
This is <i>not</i> cool!

22
00:02:39,530 --> 00:02:42,180
I set up a good match if I do say so myself.

23
00:02:42,460 --> 00:02:44,310
This should be a lively battle.

24
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:48,680
It's your bad luck to be standing 
before a member of Sabertooth.

25
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:51,310
Lucy-san, is that...

26
00:02:51,690 --> 00:02:53,980
That girl is a Celestial Spirit Wizard?!

27
00:02:56,420 --> 00:02:57,530
I don't believe it!

28
00:02:57,810 --> 00:02:59,020
There's one more?

29
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:01,320
Another Celestial Spirit Wizard...

30
00:03:02,350 --> 00:03:02,990
Huh...

31
00:03:03,670 --> 00:03:07,150
A golden key. One of those 
12 Zodiac Gate things?

32
00:03:08,070 --> 00:03:10,410
Gate of the Fish, I open thee.

33
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:14,290
Gate of the Fish! I like the sound of that!

34
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:16,310
What kind of Celestial Spirit is it?

35
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:17,620
I don't know...

36
00:03:18,270 --> 00:03:22,090
I don't think it was in the Celestial 
Spirit World when we visited.

37
00:03:22,830 --> 00:03:25,970
Going by the usual pattern, it's 
probably something like this.

38
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:29,020
That's kind of unsettling...

39
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:33,130
But there are ones like the Gemini twins too,

40
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,960
so my guess is it'll be like this.

41
00:03:35,820 --> 00:03:37,730
I have a feeling you've hit the mark...

42
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:40,110
Happy will be so pleased!

43
00:03:40,110 --> 00:03:42,000
That's not even a fish...

44
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:45,260
Wendy, don't waste your time 
contradicting that guy.

45
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:46,770
His stupidity will rub off.

46
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:48,570
Pisces!

47
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:04,970
They <i>are</i> fish!

48
00:04:11,780 --> 00:04:13,210
Don't worry!

49
00:04:13,210 --> 00:04:14,810
Take a good look.

50
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:15,600
See?

51
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:20,450
Wow!

52
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:24,020
She's dodging their attacks with 
just the slightest movements.

53
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:27,120
There are all kinds, huh?

54
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:29,310
Pisces...

55
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,520
Huh. She's not bad.

56
00:04:35,790 --> 00:04:37,770
What? She's no great shakes.

57
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:40,110
All she's doing is dodging.

58
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:42,360
Fro thinks so, too.

59
00:04:42,930 --> 00:04:44,420
Just wait and see.

60
00:04:44,850 --> 00:04:48,020
It's not wise to underestimate 
Mermaid Heel's strongest wizard.

61
00:04:48,940 --> 00:04:52,540
This looks like it's going to 
quickly become a fine magic battle.

62
00:04:53,470 --> 00:04:58,360
Whoa! She's deftly dodging 
Pisces' fierce attacks!

63
00:04:58,490 --> 00:04:59,670
Impressive.

64
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:00,780
Cool!

65
00:05:00,930 --> 00:05:03,010
Why is she escaping the fish?

66
00:05:03,350 --> 00:05:04,780
All she has to do is eat it...

67
00:05:05,150 --> 00:05:06,300
What a waste.

68
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:11,650
If you're so good at dodging, then 
all I need to do is ground you.

69
00:05:13,210 --> 00:05:14,500
Two gates open at the same time?!

70
00:05:14,890 --> 00:05:15,990
Glittering gold!

71
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:18,790
That's right! That's one of 
the 12 Zodiac Gates, too!

72
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:21,770
Gate of the Scales, I open thee.

73
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:28,770
Libra!

74
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:36,480
A-Another stunningly 
beautiful Celestial Spirit!

75
00:05:36,630 --> 00:05:38,430
She's a sight for sore eyes!

76
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:40,660
Gate of the Scales! Cool!

77
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:44,120
Libra, alter the target's gravity.

78
00:05:45,310 --> 00:05:46,000
As you wish!

79
00:05:52,710 --> 00:05:54,130
That's gravity manipulation!

80
00:05:54,670 --> 00:05:58,240
That Libra character can 
use the same magic as me?!

81
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:00,960
So she made Kagura heavier?

82
00:06:01,730 --> 00:06:02,410
Pisces...

83
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:13,650
What's this?!

84
00:06:17,030 --> 00:06:18,880
She blew off Libra's gravity power?!

85
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,020
How?

86
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:21,860
That girl's awesome!

87
00:06:22,030 --> 00:06:23,710
Her jumping ability is remarkable.

88
00:06:23,820 --> 00:06:25,350
No, that's...

89
00:06:25,940 --> 00:06:26,670
Libra...

90
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,440
Make the target's gravity go sideways.

91
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:30,830
As you wish.

92
00:06:38,150 --> 00:06:42,210
Ouch! She was only able to escape the Celestial 
Spirit's gravity altering for a short time!

93
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:44,360
Kagura is pinned to the statue!

94
00:06:44,950 --> 00:06:46,310
What a pinch!

95
00:06:46,430 --> 00:06:48,760
Gravity is cool!

96
00:06:48,940 --> 00:06:49,670
Pisces!

97
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:55,770
This is what I'm talkin' about! The 
highlight of two gates open at once!

98
00:06:56,090 --> 00:06:57,700
Highlight!

99
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:59,730
I guess it's all over...

100
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:02,940
Or I wish it would be...

101
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:12,320
The fish stopped!

102
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,400
What the...?

103
00:07:13,770 --> 00:07:14,990
Is she out of magic?

104
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:17,690
That's not it. Look at that.

105
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,250
I can't move!

106
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:24,290
I see...

107
00:07:24,810 --> 00:07:27,310
Don't tell me she can use gravity magic too?!

108
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,760
How?

109
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:33,180
Kagura's the one who taught 
me gravity-altering magic.

110
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:35,820
Better not underestimate Kagura-chan!

111
00:07:36,210 --> 00:07:37,070
That's right!

112
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:38,210
That's our...

113
00:07:38,420 --> 00:07:40,020
...Kagura-san!

114
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:42,880
Now, finish 'em all at once!

115
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:50,930
This is the epitome of the Grand Magic Games!

116
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:59,350
Oh, my! Kagura is undaunted 
by two Celestial Spirits!

117
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:01,870
This is amazing, isn't it, Yajima-san?

118
00:08:02,260 --> 00:08:06,520
Experience and grit... She 
certainly does have fortitude.

119
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:12,770
I'm so excited about getting to see a 
showdown like this right before my eyes! Cool! Cool!

120
00:08:13,170 --> 00:08:14,090
Heavy...

121
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:17,390
Pisces, Libra, go back.

122
00:08:22,140 --> 00:08:25,740
Yeesh. This is gettin' monotonous.

123
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,130
Yukino...

124
00:08:27,430 --> 00:08:30,740
She's fine! The fight is just startin'!

125
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,190
Right, Sting-kun?!

126
00:08:32,620 --> 00:08:36,200
That's right. Yukino's gonna 
bring out her real power now.

127
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:38,970
You're going to make me open...

128
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,580
...the 13th Gate?

129
00:08:44,180 --> 00:08:45,790
The 13th Gate?!

130
00:08:46,330 --> 00:08:48,390
Is that what she just said?!

131
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,980
What's wrong, Lucy-san?

132
00:08:52,050 --> 00:08:56,560
There are 12 Zodiac Gates 
and hence 12 keys...

133
00:08:57,100 --> 00:09:01,460
But I've heard rumors of a 13th key...

134
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:05,740
...and an unknown Celestial Spirit 
that's superior to the other 12!

135
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:11,750
Opening the 13th Gate... That 
means you're out of luck.

136
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,000
Luck, huh?

137
00:09:14,990 --> 00:09:17,500
I haven't relied on luck 
since the moment I was born.

138
00:09:20,090 --> 00:09:22,330
Everything has come about 
through choices that I've made!

139
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:25,460
Gate of the Serpent Bearer, I open thee!

140
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:28,880
That's what's leading me to the future!

141
00:09:29,970 --> 00:09:31,040
Ophiuchus!

142
00:09:47,010 --> 00:09:50,230
What is this?! I didn't know a 
Celestial Spirit like this existed!

143
00:09:50,370 --> 00:09:51,440
It's humongous!

144
00:09:51,610 --> 00:09:54,730
Serpent Bearer?! The thing 
itself is a serpent!

145
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:59,020
This is... Ophiuchus?!

146
00:10:03,420 --> 00:10:07,360
The 13th Gate... This is outstanding as well.

147
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:09,910
This doesn't bode well...

148
00:10:10,390 --> 00:10:17,050
Not only are there two Celestial Spirit 
Wizards here, but they both own the 12 Zodiac Gates.

149
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:26,770
Blade of Resentment, Archenemy.

150
00:10:31,310 --> 00:10:32,590
Style of the Unsheathed Sword.

151
00:10:38,790 --> 00:10:40,000
Is she for real?!

152
00:10:40,510 --> 00:10:41,800
Unsheathed...

153
00:10:43,870 --> 00:10:46,580
You really wouldn't want Kagura-chan 
to unsheathe her sword.

154
00:10:50,090 --> 00:10:50,910
I don't believe it!

155
00:10:53,350 --> 00:10:54,660
You made a cheap bet.

156
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:04,270
Sometimes, mermaids eat tigers.

157
00:11:29,710 --> 00:11:32,850
T-T-The match is over!

158
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:39,210
The winner is Kagura 
Mikazuchi of Mermaid Heel!

159
00:11:43,050 --> 00:11:44,310
I knew Kagura-chan could do it!

160
00:11:44,430 --> 00:11:45,690
Yeah!

161
00:11:45,850 --> 00:11:47,860
Told you not to underestimate Kagura!

162
00:11:48,020 --> 00:11:52,160
That Celestial Spirit Wizard is powerful in 
her own right, but Kagura is just too tough.

163
00:11:52,930 --> 00:11:57,070
It's unbelievable, but Sabertooth 
got zero points on the second day!

164
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:58,980
This is getting interesting.

165
00:11:58,980 --> 00:12:04,050
Cool! Kagura-chan is cool!

166
00:12:04,210 --> 00:12:09,730
Was the Saber woman weak? Or 
was the Mermaid woman strong?

167
00:12:10,550 --> 00:12:11,610
The latter...

168
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,360
I didn't know somebody like her existed...

169
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:19,620
I-I lost...

170
00:12:20,590 --> 00:12:22,270
Sabertooth lost...

171
00:12:22,860 --> 00:12:24,020
Yukino...

172
00:12:25,890 --> 00:12:26,840
Sting-kun...

173
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:31,150
Your life...

174
00:12:37,250 --> 00:12:39,450
Your life belongs to me.

175
00:12:40,610 --> 00:12:41,120
Understand?

176
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:43,540
Yes.

177
00:12:45,060 --> 00:12:46,130
As you say...

178
00:12:47,590 --> 00:12:51,160
And thus ends the second day 
of the Grand Magic Games!

179
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:56,950
Raven Tail gained ten points today, 
giving them first place with 36 points!

180
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,140
Sabertooth gained zero points today,

181
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:02,380
but their 20 points from yesterday 
keeps them in second place!

182
00:13:02,890 --> 00:13:07,380
Likewise, Lamia Scale is tied 
in second with 20 points!

183
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:15,270
And Mermaid Heel is moving up. They gained ten 
points, putting them in fourth place with 19 points.

184
00:13:15,450 --> 00:13:18,940
In fifth place, one rank down, 
is Blue Pegasus with 17 points!

185
00:13:19,070 --> 00:13:20,520
Cool!

186
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:24,980
And in sixth place, one rank 
down for them, Quatro Puppy!

187
00:13:25,110 --> 00:13:27,010
S-Seriously?!

188
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:33,570
Um... Our guild name has 
become Quatro Puppy...

189
00:13:34,350 --> 00:13:37,300
Can't help it. A promise 
was made between two men.

190
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:42,700
Alright! I'm gonna drink 
again tonight! Wild...

191
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:44,550
...Four...

192
00:13:45,110 --> 00:13:52,630
And gaining ten points each, but still 
tied in last place, are Fairy Tail A Team

193
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:57,000
and Fairy Tail B Team, both with 12 points!

194
00:13:57,590 --> 00:14:01,770
What kind of battles are in store for us 
tomorrow, the third day of the tournament?!

195
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:04,590
Those were some fine magic battles.

196
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:11,250
Another Celestial Spirit Wizard...

197
00:14:11,900 --> 00:14:13,720
It must be destiny...

198
00:14:15,110 --> 00:14:18,330
Now the project is even 
more certain to succeed.

199
00:14:19,330 --> 00:14:21,080
This can't go on.

200
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:23,730
I have to do something quickly...

201
00:14:25,540 --> 00:14:26,740
It <i>is</i> strange...

202
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:33,630
Even though the second day is over, I haven't 
sensed the magic power that I perceive every year.

203
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:37,720
The second day of the 
Grand Magic Games ended.

204
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:41,720
Five more days until that fateful day...

205
00:14:46,410 --> 00:14:47,710
You don't sense the magic power?

206
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:49,210
Right.

207
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:53,580
The power that was similar to 
Zeref's, that we felt every year...

208
00:14:54,740 --> 00:14:56,740
I haven't sensed it this time, not yet.

209
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:58,500
What does it mean?

210
00:14:59,090 --> 00:15:01,470
I can think of many possibilities.

211
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:04,930
If it came from a person,

212
00:15:05,820 --> 00:15:07,890
maybe they're not in Crocus this time.

213
00:15:08,670 --> 00:15:11,940
Or maybe they're in Crocus, 
but not using the power.

214
00:15:12,660 --> 00:15:16,980
It's also possible that they're a contestant 
in the Games, but haven't participated yet.

215
00:15:17,610 --> 00:15:22,600
If that magic is from some kind 
of device or a set location,

216
00:15:23,510 --> 00:15:25,250
perhaps the device isn't in operation,

217
00:15:25,740 --> 00:15:29,150
or there's some sort of filter that 
keeps the magic from leaking outside.

218
00:15:30,090 --> 00:15:34,680
At any rate, as long as you don't sense that 
dangerous power, nothing should happen.

219
00:15:35,670 --> 00:15:36,980
I hope you're right.

220
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:41,060
Maybe I'll check out the 
organizers from tomorrow.

221
00:15:42,110 --> 00:15:43,850
Don't do anything to stand out.

222
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:48,550
I know. Ultear already reminded me.

223
00:15:51,850 --> 00:15:53,150
And try not to get yourself killed.

224
00:15:54,890 --> 00:15:57,840
Got it. Goodnight, Erza.

225
00:15:58,920 --> 00:15:59,380
Yeah.

226
00:16:11,420 --> 00:16:15,040
I never thought the day would come 
when we could talk normally like this.

227
00:16:16,690 --> 00:16:18,490
Thank you, Erza.

228
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:27,870
It's gotten late. Is the 
dinner party over already?

229
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:29,950
I found you at last!

230
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:31,080
Who are you?!

231
00:16:32,990 --> 00:16:34,030
Feelin' spiffy?!

232
00:16:39,630 --> 00:16:41,520
Feelin' spiffy!

233
00:16:43,070 --> 00:16:43,820
You...

234
00:16:45,590 --> 00:16:47,230
Er-chan, long time no see!

235
00:16:48,490 --> 00:16:49,780
Millianna!

236
00:16:51,090 --> 00:16:52,650
I missed you!

237
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:55,360
Millianna!

238
00:16:56,170 --> 00:16:57,520
You're in a guild?

239
00:16:57,890 --> 00:16:59,980
Yep. Mermaid Heel.

240
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:02,750
Are Sho and Wally in the same guild?

241
00:17:03,740 --> 00:17:07,930
What are you talking about? Mermaid 
Heel is a women-only guild!

242
00:17:08,710 --> 00:17:09,370
I see.

243
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:14,420
Those two are still traveling. I 
hear from them once in a while.

244
00:17:15,710 --> 00:17:20,790
I see. It really is great 
to see you, Millianna.

245
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,810
Me too, Er-chan.

246
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:27,440
I'm so happy to see you doing well.

247
00:17:29,730 --> 00:17:31,970
Er-chan, don't cry!

248
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,850
What about you?!

249
00:17:38,910 --> 00:17:40,910
Alright, another round!

250
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:43,620
My soul is always Wild...

251
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:45,740
...Four!

252
00:17:47,010 --> 00:17:48,830
You guys are good sports!

253
00:17:48,830 --> 00:17:51,090
Same goes for you!

254
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:54,660
It's gettin' pretty late. We better 
start headin' back to the inn.

255
00:17:55,030 --> 00:17:56,760
Erza hasn't come yet!

256
00:17:56,910 --> 00:17:58,280
Now that you mention it, she is late...

257
00:17:58,530 --> 00:18:01,150
She mentioned having something to do.

258
00:18:01,430 --> 00:18:03,470
Are your hands okay?

259
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:06,550
Nothin' a good night's sleep can't fix!

260
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:08,150
We're wild, right?

261
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:11,890
Oh yeah, I almost forgot.

262
00:18:12,590 --> 00:18:14,770
That guy's name is Elfman, yeah?

263
00:18:15,590 --> 00:18:17,210
Give him a message for me.

264
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:20,730
Tell him it was a wild battle...

265
00:18:21,210 --> 00:18:25,090
An' I'm lookin' forward to goin' up 
against him again during the tournament.

266
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:30,410
I'll tell him. I wanna fight you myself.

267
00:18:30,540 --> 00:18:32,500
We're gonna beat you again next time, too!

268
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:35,920
Man!

269
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:37,800
Four!

270
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:40,800
Jeez... Enough already...

271
00:18:40,980 --> 00:18:42,110
By the way, where's Gramps?

272
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:45,600
He was having a drinking 
contest with Bacchus-san...

273
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:47,910
He's probably on the floor over there.

274
00:18:48,550 --> 00:18:49,340
Lu-chan?

275
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,530
Sorry we woke you up...

276
00:18:54,030 --> 00:18:55,300
Never mind about that.

277
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:58,430
What's wrong? You look down.

278
00:18:59,110 --> 00:19:02,730
Yeah... I was thinking about 
Saber's Celestial Spirit Wizard...

279
00:19:03,430 --> 00:19:05,660
Yukino-san, I think her name is, right?

280
00:19:06,490 --> 00:19:13,630
That was amazing. The 12 Zodiac Gates and 
the 13th one... I think? Even though she lost...

281
00:19:14,670 --> 00:19:20,180
They said they bet their lives, so I was 
wondering what's gonna happen now...

282
00:19:20,930 --> 00:19:22,720
True, it is worrisome...

283
00:19:24,150 --> 00:19:26,940
Even though we're in no position 
to be worried about other people...

284
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:30,960
What? We've still got three days left!

285
00:19:33,270 --> 00:19:37,230
You're right. First, we need to 
focus on winning and do our best!

286
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:41,740
Hey! You guys got a visitor. They're in here.

287
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:50,800
Leon and... Sherry's cousin.

288
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:53,570
Cheria-san, right?

289
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:56,980
This looks like it's gonna be a pain...

290
00:20:04,030 --> 00:20:08,340
This is Crocus Garden, the inn 
where Sabertooth is staying.

291
00:20:14,230 --> 00:20:18,030
It's so pitiful that I 
can't even cry, you scum.

292
00:20:19,050 --> 00:20:23,450
Remember why we're the top wizard guild.

293
00:20:24,030 --> 00:20:29,700
Don't look at the insects around you. 
Don't talk to them. Just crush them.

294
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:33,710
Our eyes are on something far greater.

295
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:40,510
Making the heavens roar. Setting the 
land aflame. Silencing the seas.

296
00:20:42,050 --> 00:20:44,360
That's Sabertooth.

297
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:50,420
This man is Sabertooth's master, Gemma.

298
00:20:51,180 --> 00:20:51,900
Sting...

299
00:20:52,490 --> 00:20:53,190
Yes?

300
00:20:53,930 --> 00:20:56,870
I'll give you just one more chance.

301
00:20:57,510 --> 00:21:00,270
Don't you ever make such 
a pathetic scene again.

302
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:06,030
Thank you. I swear that I'll 
measure up to your expectations.

303
00:21:07,930 --> 00:21:08,890
Yukino...

304
00:21:09,540 --> 00:21:10,200
Yes.

305
00:21:11,810 --> 00:21:14,370
You have no excuse.

306
00:21:15,060 --> 00:21:16,720
You do know that?

307
00:21:17,670 --> 00:21:18,460
Yes.

308
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:28,990
I lost to the member of another guild. 
I brought shame to Sabertooth.

309
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:32,970
That's not what I'm talking about!

310
00:21:34,140 --> 00:21:40,000
You wagered your life and lost, and not 
only that, the enemy took pity on you!

311
00:21:40,540 --> 00:21:42,850
On Sabertooth!

312
00:21:43,170 --> 00:21:43,890
Yes.

313
00:21:44,460 --> 00:21:48,510
I will submit to any punishment.

314
00:21:50,360 --> 00:21:53,210
Then throw away everything.

315
00:21:55,410 --> 00:21:58,110
Yes. I will do exactly as you say.

316
00:22:00,150 --> 00:22:04,420
And so ended the second day 
of the Grand Magic Games.

317
00:22:05,530 --> 00:22:11,130
Somehow, Fairy Tail emerged as a contender, 
even while staying in last place,

318
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:13,610
but on the underside of 
the spectacular festival,

319
00:22:13,610 --> 00:22:18,980
something most of them never dreamed 
of was slowly set into motion.

320
00:23:55,850 --> 00:23:59,330
Pop quiz! Who's going to pay a visit now?

321
00:23:59,330 --> 00:24:01,890
Where's this comin' from?! 
How the hell would I know?

322
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:05,350
Then I'll give you a hint. What are those 
white crystals that fall from the sky in winter?

323
00:24:05,350 --> 00:24:06,310
Y-Yuki...

324
00:24:05,350 --> 00:24:06,310
snow

325
00:24:06,310 --> 00:24:07,760
What's the opposite of yes?

326
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:08,190
No!

327
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:10,850
If you put 'em together, you'll 
pretty much have the answer!

328
00:24:10,930 --> 00:24:12,620
Yuki-no!

329
00:24:12,730 --> 00:24:13,470
Natsu...

330
00:24:13,650 --> 00:24:16,600
Next time: Grudges Are Wrapped 
in the Silence of the Night!

331
00:24:17,210 --> 00:24:17,920
Yuki-no, right?

332
00:24:18,210 --> 00:24:23,280
Natsu, you know who it is but 
you're saying it weird on purpose!

333
00:24:23,280 --> 00:24:25,280


